def: The quality or state of being variable; variability. James i.17.
A spring-blooming plant (Fritillaria imperialis) of the Lilyfamily, having at the top of the stalk a cluster of pendent bell-shaped flowers surmounted with a tuft of green leaves.
An extinct group of Mammalia found fossil in the Eoceneformation. The species are related to the carnivores, ungulates, androdents. Called also Tillodonta.
Pertaining to, containing, or resembling, oxygen; producingoxygen.
Any minute fungus which produces a burnt appearance in plants.The brands are of many species and several genera of the orderPucciniæi.
The act reëdifying; the state of being reëdified.
Quality or state of mind. "The same hard mentality." Emerson.

A volatile liquid hydrocarbon, C5H6, related to ethylene andacetylene, but possessing the property of unsaturation in the thirddegree. It is the only known member of a distinct series ofcompounds. It has a garlic odor.
A speaking or conversing together; conference; mutualdiscourse. Bailey.
The slender, hollow thread of a nettling cell or cnida. SeeNettling cell. [Written also ecthoræum.]
